title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that calculates waiting list totals for each municipality. The plan must filter the waiting list data for the month “2025-05” first. We want two values computed. The total per waiting list type and the overall total for the municipality. The output must be sorted in descending order by the municipality’s total. Output in textfile.

operations.udf: (a: (Int, String, Int), b: (Int, String, Int)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)
(t: ((Int, String, Int), (Int, String))) => { val rec = t._1; val org = t._2; (org._2, rec._2, rec._3) }
(t: ((String, String, Int), (String, Int))) => { val typeRow = t._1; val overall = t._2; (typeRow._1, typeRow._2, typeRow._3, overall._2) }
(t: (String, String, Int, Int)) => s"${t._1} | type=${t._2} | type_total=${t._3} | municipality_total=${t._4}"

log.thoughts: Filter waiting lists to 2025-05, aggregate per (org, type), map org to municipality, compute per-municipality totals, attach overall totals to each type row, then sort by municipality total descending and write to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, year_month, waiting_list_type, total FROM factwaitinglists) as X

data.udf: (a: (Int, String, Int), b: (Int, String, Int)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3)

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, municipality FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (t: ((Int, String, Int), (Int, String))) => { val rec = t._1; val org = t._2; (org._2, rec._2, rec._3) }
(t: ((String, String, Int), (String, Int))) => { val typeRow = t._1; val overall = t._2; (typeRow._1, typeRow._2, typeRow._3, overall._2) }
(t: (String, String, Int, Int)) => s"${t._1} | type=${t._2} | type_total=${t._3} | municipality_total=${t._4}"

title: Wayang: Wayang plan sent to Wayang
